Raw payroll data stored in S3 is processed through AWS Glue ETL and stored as Optimized parquet files for analytical queries.

Technologies Used:
•	AWS S3
•	AWS Glue
•	PySpark
•	Parquet format
•	Amazon Athena

ETL Process:
The ETL job performs the following steps:
1. Read payroll CSV dataset from S3
2. Cleans column names
3. Casts numeric columns to correct data types
4. Filters invalid salary rows
5. Writes processed data in Parquet format
